# UX fallback: a colon suffix that is NOT a clean number is never silently mangled — the
# address stays as typed and the explicit port step still runs.
desc wizard: non-numeric colon suffix falls back to the separate port step
pick 0|https (secure, recommended)
kb 0|romm.example.com:80a8
kb 0|8443
pick 0|Verify TLS certificate (recommended)
engine 0|RESULT server_set=1
kb 2|
pick 2|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace KB[Port (leave blank for default)]
expect_trace ENGINE --set-server https://romm.example.com:80a8 --port 8443 -> rc=0
